This paper deals with the problem of finding common zeros of quadratic polynomials, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and has applications in cryptanalysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves sparse linear algebra, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses complexity bounds and algorithms, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
